			<p><a href="images/tut_img/flowchart.jpg"><img class="right" width="45%" src="images/tut_img/flowchart.jpg"></a>However, there are a few things that almost any fortress will NEED. I’ll go over our immediate short-term goals here and get us started by building some initial workshops, a wall or two, and most importantly, stairs down into the ground and a nice subterranean set of rooms. Additionally, we’ll plan ahead for cleanliness and resources.</p>
			<p>The <a href="http://dwarffortresswiki.org/index.php/DF2012:Quickstart_guide" target="_blank">quickstart</a> guide on the wiki is a VERY good resource, and will probably mirror my own suggestions for the most part (because I used it extensively when I was learning).</p>
			<p><a href="images/tut_img/flowchart.jpg">This chart</a> probably looks like gibberish at this point, but follow along and you’ll get the swing of things. It’s a flowchart describing the general order of operations when embarking. I have one printed out!</p>	
