		<div id="cont_right">
			<p><strong>NEED #1</strong>: You need to get out of the open and into the Earth, either straight down into the ground or by digging into a nearby hillside. Don’t worry yet about traps or defense unless you’ve embarked in a wild or evil area, goblins usually do not arrive to harass you for a year, perhaps two. And your wagon has a temporary supply of food and drink, hopefully enough to last until you get a decent set of rooms dug out.</p>
			<p><a href="http://dwarffortresswiki.org/index.php/DF2012:Design_strategies" target="_blank">Fortress design</a> and layout is varied and (can be) intricate, and everyone has their own style.  Some people build elaborate fractal designs, others build very simple hallways and rooms.  For now we should just concentrate on getting the rooms functional and getting everyone inside and dwarfy.</p>
